-->PICK OF THE WEEK:
ICQ 99B BETA
File size: 5MB
License: Freeware
Minimum requirements: Windows 95/98/NT
What's the most robust instant messenger out there? ICQ still reigns
supreme. The latest version of the ubiquitous instant messenger now packs
several new features, including a new ActiveList that lets you create or
join ICQ communities based on your interests, improved email-handling
with added support for multiple email accounts, and more. In addition,
the new "E-ICQ" feature lets you join interest groups and receive related
information directly in your Contact List. Improved flower power:
