7. The Emailbag
>Haven't you got any decent screensavers? Most of the ones you advise us
>about are either gory, violent, or distasteful. How about a Walt Disney
>screensaver? Or a Toys-R-Us screensaver? Or Nature? Or skydiving? Or
>skiing? Or seas? Or ships? Hope these suggestions are sufficient to
>inspire you.
CNET Download.com responds:
Hi Wendy, with the amount of violence and gore in the world today, we can
understand why you might not want constant reminders of the seamy side of
life floating around your desktop. But don't give up hope yet! We have
quite an extensive screensaver library over here at CNET Download.com,
including a variety of "G-rated" screensavers. Check 'em out:
http://www.download.com/DD/dl/0,302,0-0817-1-044,00.html
Check out our entire collection of screensavers:
http://www.download.com/DD/dl/0,302,0-0817-1-045,00.html
Got a question about downloading? Send it on to comments@download.com
